  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "XJk6C58NpPrHBdEQDgtIh/MS7oE=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# operation design uses descriptive names and includes examples and errors\n\nWell-designed operations have three qualities:\n\n1. **Descriptive names** \u2014 `ADD_LINE_ITEM`, `UPDATE_RECIPIENT`, `SET_DUE_DATE` (not `UPDATE_DATA` or `MODIFY`)\n2. **Comprehensive examples** \u2014 Added via `ADD_OPERATION_EXAMPLE` to demonstrate expected inputs and outputs\n3. **Specific error definitions** \u2014 Added via `ADD_OPERATION_ERROR` with patterns like `EntityNotFoundError`, `DuplicateIdError`, `InvalidInputError`\n\nSince [[one operation per user intent keeps concerns separated]], each operation maps to exactly one user action. Since [[error names must end with Error and use PascalCase]], error definitions follow strict naming conventions.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z"
    }
  },
